input_str: Is it really a wrap for King of the Hill? Fox has canceled the show after 13 seasons (it’s the second-longest running sitcom currently on the air, after The Simpsons). Late last week, a few dozen guests were invited to sit in on the table read for the final episode, which was followed by the voice talent all posing alongside a huge celebratory cake baked in the shape of a propane grill.
